This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by Donald J. Trump on April 4, 2017. The memorandum outlines the organization of the National Security Council (NSC), the Homeland Security Council (HSC), and their subcommittees. It emphasizes the importance of ensuring the safety and security of the American people, and states that both the NSC and HSC will continue to be chaired by the President. The memorandum also lists the regular attendees of the NSC and HSC meetings, which include various heads of executive departments and agencies. It establishes the Principals Committee (PC) as the senior interagency forum for considering policy issues related to national security and the Deputies Committee (DC) as the sub-Cabinet interagency forum for decision-making on policy issues. The memorandum also mentions the establishment of Policy Coordination Committees (PCCs) to manage the development and implementation of national security policies. The document concludes by stating that it supersedes all other existing Presidential directives and guidance on the organization of the NSC and HSC.